"HELLO CITY SERVICES, NEVER MIND. THE DEAD raccoon is gone. The dead coon was still there Tuesday afternoon AFTER your workers said they had visited and ""could not locate"" the critter.This is a follow-up message to #SR14013438, which is itself a follow-up to #SR14013191. I had initially requested a Dead Animal Removal. The city worker who, apparently, came looking for it stated ""by 882 could not locate"". That was Tuesday 2/18 12:32 PM. At 1:30 pm I texted my wife at home, asking her to look for the dead raccoon. She replied: ""They didn't look very hard. I saw it in 10 secs outside window. It's lying in a bunch of leaves, which might obscure if you were looking from a distance, but not if you actually walked back there. Dorks."" I apologize for my wife, describing City Service personnel as ""dorks"", but I must admit I am not particularly impressed with Cincinnati City Services during this whole interaction."
